<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Hong Kong's Return Opens in Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENTIANE, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition opened here
today to mark China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Saysomphone Phomvihan, Lao's Finance Minister and Chairman of
the Laos-China Friendship Association, attended the opening
ceremony of the exhibition which is held in the National Museum.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also attracted senior Laotian government and
party officials, some foreign ambassadors and local Chinese
community representatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
