<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Morocco Beats Host Malaysia 3-1 in World Youth Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHAH ALAM, Malaysia, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Morocco came from
behind to beat host Malaysia 3-1 in the opening match of the World
Youth Football Championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia took the lead 1-0 by scoring in the 10th minute of the
Group A match at 71,000-seat Shah Alam stadium on the outskirts of
Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
Moroccan defender Safri Youssef kicked the ball inside his own
goal when he attempted to thwart a Malaysian attack.
</P>
<P>
The African junior champion Morocco soon drew level four
minutes later on a goal by Tariq Sektiouito.
</P>
<P>
Khalid Khamma netted one in the 31st minute to give Morocco a
2-1 lead before the break.
</P>
<P>
Aissam Barroudi broke through in the last minute to seal the
Moroccan victory.
</P>
<P>
Morocco now need to draw one of their remaining league matches
against Uruguay or Belgium to qualify for the last 16.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-four teams are competing in six groups at the
preliminary stage of the three-week-long tournament, which include
defending champions Argentina, Brazil, France, England and China.
</P>
<P>
The top two teams in each group and four best third-place
finishers will qualify for the 16-team knock-out rounds. The final
will be played on July 5.
</P>
<P>
Before the match there was a colorful opening ceremony, which
was attended by acting prime minister Seri Anwar Ibrahim,
International Football Federation president Joao Havelange and
general secretary Joseph Blatter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
