<HEADLINE> Chechnya Launches Anti-Crime Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Chechen President Aslan Maskhadov
today ordered the resumption of the anti-crime "Shield of Law"
operation in Chechnya, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the operation is to put an end to kidnapping, drug
addiction, unlawful seizure of housing facilities, and to enforce
law and order in the republic's petroleum industry, Chechen
Interior Minister Kazbek Makhashev said.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the "Shield of Law" operation, six hostages were
released from captivity today.
</P>
<P>
Alongside with the "Shield of Law", another operation
code-named "Hostages", was also launched Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Maskhadov promised to "deal surprise and
lightning-fast strikes" in the crackdown on crime in the republic,
when Russia and the breakaway republic were discussing economic
cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
