<HEADLINE> Trason Wins Comrades Marathon Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Ann Trason of the United
States won her second straight women's Comrades Marathon race in
Durban, South Africa on Monday, while South African
Charl Mattheus won the men's race.
</P>
<P>
Trason, the world's 100-kilometer record holder, came from
behind to catch Germany's Maria Bak in the 89-kilometer
ultramarathon that is South Africa's premier race.
</P>
<P>
Trason clocked five hours, 58 minutes and 27 seconds and Bak
was runner-up after clocking 6:00.28 for the second straight year.
</P>
<P>
Mattheus finished first in the men's race with a time of
5:28.37 followed by Nick Bester in 5:30.41 and Poland's Joroslaw
Janicki in 5:32.50. 
</P>
</TEXT>
