<HEADLINE> DDC Elections in Nepal Rescheduled for July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Election Commission of Nepal
announced here today that elections for district development
committees (DDC) have been rescheduled for July 11.
</P>
<P>
The DDC elections will be held in the districts of four
development regions, the commission said, adding that elections in
the Mid-Western Development Region will take place following
village development committee (VDC) elections in the ultra
leftist-affected districts, where candidates failed to file
nomination papers, bowing to threats from the ultra leftists.
</P>
<P>
The local elections have been divided into three phases.
Elections in 3,192 VDCs and 58 municipalities took place on May 17
and May 26 respectively while the elections for 75 DDCs scheduled
for June 20 have been put off until July 11.  
</P>
</TEXT>
