<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inter-clan Fighting Continues in Southern Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The inter-clan fighting
continued in the southern Somali port town of Kismaio for the
second day today.
</P>
<P>
The rival militiamen of Marchan and Majerten have exchanged
attack and counter-attack around the outskirts of the town early
today.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from the local field radios, the port
town of Kismaio is once again falling into renewed clan-based
rivalry over the control of the strategic town for the first time
for nearly four years.
</P>
<P>
The hostility has been growing ever since the Marehans had
been driven out of the town early this year, and only now their
militiamen have started guerrilla fighting against the Majertens.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fighting is reported in the villages of Gobwein and
Madhamato just outside the town where the opposing sides have
suffered heavy casualties.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said more than 13 people died and more than 25
others were wounded today, thus bringing the total death to at
least 23 and more than 40 injuries since yesterday.
</P>
<P>
This new round of hostility in the second most sensitive
region after Mogadishu is worsening the already lingering
humanitarian condition of Kismaio. Negotiation attempts made by
the clan leaders of the warring sides have brought about no
fruits so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
