<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motorola Ships First 300 MHz System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Motorola Computer Group of
the U.S. announced today that it is the first computer
manufacturer to ship a PowerPC-based 300 MHz system.
</P>
<P>
The new Motorola StarMax 5000/300 is the first shipping Mac
OS-compatible system to break the 300 MHz speed barrier, according
to the company. Based on the PowerPC 603e chip, the speed and
components of the StarMax 5000/300 are designed to support the
user who needs access to several applications, such as word
processing, database, presentation and web access software, at one
time.
</P>
<P>
The StarMax 5000/300 minitower system includes Mac OS 7.6, 32
MB RAM, 16x CD-ROM drive, 4.3 GB drive and an Ethernet adaptor.
</P>
<P>
In addition, several utility software packages are included
with the StarMax 5000/300.
</P>
<P>
Motorola also offers a graphics-enhanced version of the same
model which allows monitors to be connected to both video adapters
simultaneously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
