<HEADLINE> 7,000 Orphans in Lusaka Get Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 7,000 orphaned children
in Lusaka have got help with all the basic needs from Children In
Distress (CINDI), a non-governmental organization (NGO), since
its inception in 1994.
</P>
<P>
A latest report from the CINDI said its aim is to alleviate
the suffering of the orphans in the city. As a NGO, CINDI is
trying to tackle the huge challenge of the growing number of
orphans, some of whom have lost both parents.
</P>
<P>
The organization's dreams are to care for the children,
provide education and medical facilities and to start small self
help projects for those out of school, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The CINDI has already started three small agricultural
projects to help children who are not in school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
