<HEADLINE> Bahrain Regrets US Congress Move on Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain' parliament today
expressed resentment over a US Congress resolution declaring
Jerusalem as the "undivided capital of Israel" and sanctioning
funds for shifting the US embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain's parliament said in a statement issued today that the
US Congress decision was a threat to the Middle East peace process
and was against internation rules, particularly the UN 242
resolution which calls for Israeli withdrawal from all occupied
Arab lands.
</P>
<P>
The parliament also said that the U.S. vote has hurt the
sentiment of the Islamic and Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The non-binding resolution, opposed by Clinton administration,
was passed on Tuesday and has since sparked criticism and
condemnation from among the Arab world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
