<HEADLINE> Angolan President Willing to Meet UNITA Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo Dos
Santos is always willing to meet UNITA leader Jonas Savimbi, but
he proposes that such a meeting should be held on the territory
of Angola, a diplomat said here today.
</P>
<P>
Angolan ambassador to Portugal Jose Patricio said in an
interview with the Portugal TV Station that with the
establishment of the Angolan government of national unity and
reconciliation, next meeting between Dos Santos and Savimbi
should be held in their motherland in order to promote the
credibility of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The venue for such a meeting can be anywhere in Angola, not
limited to Luanda, he said, reacting to Savimbi's recent remarks
which suggested that next meeting between him and Dos Santos
still be held in a foreign country, such as Italy.
</P>
<P>
The UNITA leader and President Dos Santos is due to hold their
fifth meeting in recent two years. Their last four meetings have
been held outside their own country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
