<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition in Iraq Marks Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition about the
history and development of Hong Kong opened today at the
Saddam Art Center in Baghdad to mark Hong Kong's return
to China.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the exhibition sponsored by the
Chinese embassy in Iraq, Hamed Yousuf Hamadi, minister of
Information and Culture congratulated the Chinese people and
government on Hong Kong's return to its motherland.
</P>
<P>
He wrote on the visitor's book that Hong Kong's return to
China is not only a great victory of the Chinese people
over colonialism, but also a great victory of the third world
and all the people who love peace and freedom.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Sun Bigan and Abdul Illah Mohammed, minister
of Iraqi Agriculture also attended the opening ceremony..
</P>
<P>
About one hundred carefully chosen photographs covering the
history of Hong Kong, the process of Hong Kong's return and
Hong Kong today are displayed at the three-day exhibition.
</P>
