<HEADLINE> Program of Action for Children and Women Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The national program of
action for children and women was officially launched in Ethiopia
today in commemoration of the Day of the African Child.
</P>
<P>
The program which covers health, food and nutrition, water
supply and sanitation and education gives priority to children in
especially difficult circumstances, the advancement of women,
combating environmental degradation and emergencies.
</P>
<P>
When launching the program here, Ethiopian President Negasso
Gidada said in Ethiopia, the Convention of the Rights of the
Child having been ratified by the transitional government.
</P>
<P>
He called upon friendly governments, international
organizations and others to stand by the government of Ethiopia
and provide the necessary support for the success of the noble
objective.
</P>
<P>
June 16 was named in July 1990 by the 26th summit of African
heads of state and government as the Day of the African Child to
commemorate South African students' struggle against apartheid.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's African Children Day is "education of
the girl child" because it is viewed as being key to national
development in Africa. 
</P>
