<HEADLINE> Russia, Cyprus on Arms Supplies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov said today that Russia will continue to supply defensive
weapons to Cyprus, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with his Cypriot counterpart,
Yiannakis Cassoulides, today, Primakov said that Russia cannot
deliver these weapons to Cyprus unless it declares a
demilitarized zone and demilitarized order is indeed established
there.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus issue has long been a sore spot in Europe. Primakov
said Russia is interested in its peaceful and speedy resolution.
He hoped that its settlement should ensure the security of both
communities living in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Cassoulides expressed satisfaction with the relations between
Cyprus and Russia, calling the relations "exemplary."
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot minister said the U.N.-brokered talks on the Cyprus
conflict settlement will be held in New York in early July. He
believed Russia could play an important role at these talks as a
permanent member of the U.N. Security Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
