<HEADLINE> Canadian Ports Handle Record Foreign Cargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Canadian ports handled a record
tonnage of international cargo last year, said a newspaper report
today.
</P>
<P>
Canadian ports handled 358 million tons of cargo in 1996, down
0.7 percent from 1995. International shipments totaled 260 million
tons, up 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, domestic cargo shipments have been on a
decade-long slide and fell 3.1 percent in 1996, the report quoted
Statistics Canada as saying.
</P>
<P>
Vancouver was the busiest Canadian port, which handled nearly
27 percent of the country's international shipments last year.
</P>
<P>
Higher movements of coal and sulphur contributed to a 2.5
percent rise in international shipments through the Vancouver
port. 
</P>
</TEXT>
