<HEADLINE> Liberian Politicians Begin Election Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Liberia's election campaign for a
new democratic government started today as scheduled despite
reportedly poor preparations for the country's first election
after six years of civil war.
</P>
<P>
A Nigerian Television Authority report showed that all the 11
presidential candidates signed the documents in Monrovia, capital
of Liberia, to kick off their election campaign.
</P>
<P>
The three former warlords, Charles Taylor of the National
Patriotic Party, Alhaji Kromah of the All Liberia Coalition Party
and George Boley of the National Democratic Party, are among the
presidential racers.
</P>
<P>
The election, slated for July 19, will produce a president, a
vice-president and a 90-member parliament.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said preparations for the election were not
sufficient as voters' education had not begun even in Monrovia
and polling centers had yet to be named, while the electoral
commission had not got enough money to do its work.
</P>
<P>
However, as the campaign has begun, Liberians surviving the
six-year fraternal killing that claimed the lives of more than
200,000 people and left more others homeless will have a taste of
ballot. 
</P>
