<HEADLINE> Minister Says Mideast Peace to Dominate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Mideast peace process will
dominate the summit between Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and
his French counterpart Jacques Chirac in Paris Thursday, Egyptian
Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said today.
</P>
<P>
The summit during the visit of Mubarak to France is part of the
coordination and consultations held by the two leaders on
salvaging the Mideast peace process and exploring ways to bolster
the Euro-Mediterranean cooperation and bilateral relations, said
Moussa.
</P>
