<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-16 20:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mahatir Calls for Israel-Arab Good-Neighborliness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahatir Mohammed today called for "good-neighborliness and
sincerity" between Israel and surrounding Arab states, stressing
that violence is not a solution to Israel's security problems.
</P>
<P>
Mahatir, who arrived here this afternoon as the first Malaysian
premier ever to visit Lebanon, made the remark while addressing a
dinner held by Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri in his honor.
</P>
<P>
Mahatir said that any country that forcibly takes over land
and properties belonging to others and destroys other people's
homes in order to impose its own settlements "can not be said
sincere in seeking peace."
</P>
<P>
Yet Israel tries to justify its aggressive actions by accusing
its Arab neighbors of threatening to retaliate, "if others can
not retaliate or even can not threaten to retaliate, then all
aggressions must be condoned," the Malaysian premier noted.
</P>
<P>
"What kind of world we will create, if aggression, and
disregard for world opinion, is considered as right?" he asked.
</P>
<P>
"Israel must learn to reject violence as solution for its
so-called 'security problems'," Mahatir said.
</P>
<P>
"Violence is not the solution," he underlined, "Good
neighborliness and sincerity are."
</P>
<P>
He expressed his country's sympathy with Lebanon, whose
one-tenth territory has been occupied by Israel since 1978, and
support for U.N. Security Council Resolution 425, which calls for
an unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
"The current Israeli government must also honor commitments
made by its preceding government," he said, and asked if a new
government ignores all the promises made by its predecessors, "how
do we conduct international relations?"
</P>
<P>
"Peace can only come about with sacrifice." he added.
</P>
<P>
"No one, Arab, Palestinian or Muslim, regards Jews as his
eternal enemy. What Israel is required is a change in the current
Israeli government's mind-set which condemns Muslims and Arabs as
their eternal enemy. This mind-set prevents any progress towards
peace," Mahatir said.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day official visit, the Malaysian prime
minister will hold meetings with his Lebanese counterpart Hariri,
Lebanese President Elias Hrawi, House Speaker Nabih Berri and
other ranking officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
