<HEADLINE> China Completes Relief Grain Shipment to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAMPO, DPRK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China has completed the
delivery of this year's 70,000-ton relief grain to the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) with the last 10,000-ton
shipment arriving today at the country's western seaport of Nampo.
</P>
<P>
The grain aid committed by the Chinese government on April 12
comprised 10,000 tons of rice and 60,000 tons of corn. The first
shipment began on May 20.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China provided DPRK with a total of 120,000 tons of
grain to help alleviate its food shortage arising from serious
floods. 
