<HEADLINE> Reporters Boycott British Press Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Journalists boycotted here today
a press conference of the visiting British Secretary of State for
Foreign Affairs Derek Fatchett in protest against the "unfair"
attitude of the British High Commission's security staff.
</P>
<P>
Fatchett, who arrived here Sunday for a three-day visit to
Pakistan, is scheduled to talk to the press at 5 p.m. today at the
commission.
</P>
<P>
About a dozen journalists from leading local publications and
foreign news agencies were kept waiting for 15 to 20 minutes
outside the commission in the sweltering heat.
</P>
<P>
Today's outdoor temperature was above 40 degrees Celsius,
according to weather forecasts.
</P>
<P>
The journalists who tried in vain to persuade the security
guards to open the iron gate eventually got angry and decided to
boycott the news conference.
</P>
<P>
Most of the journalists complained to a commission official,
who came to the spot at 5:05 p.m. to ask them in, that it is the
routine practice of the security staff to keep reporters waiting
on the pretext of some security reasons.  
</P>
