<HEADLINE> Pollution along Huaihe River to be Controlled by Year End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Song Jian said
here today that effective measure should be taken to ensure that
by the year's end, industrial enterprises along the Huaihe River
in central and eastern China will discharge water in accordance
with national standards.
</P>
<P>
Song, also head of the Environmental Protection Committee of
the State Council, said at a conference held by the committee that
the task will be difficult.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, some departments under the State
Council and local governments of Henan, Anhui, Jiangsu and
Shandong provinces have exerted great efforts to control and
prevent pollution in the Huaihe River valley, Song said.
</P>
<P>
And local governments have raised funds and enacted regulations
to clamp down on some polluting enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He called on local officials to do more to urge industrial
enterprises to be conscientious in treatment of wastewater, so
that it can meet national standards.
</P>
<P>
Those enterprises which cannot meet the standards as scheduled
must be shut down, Song noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
