<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Urges Measures to Deal With Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina today directed the concerned authorities to take necessary
measures to cope with the situation arising from a gas-ignited
devastating fire raging in Magurchhara Gas Field since early
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
While visiting the drilling site of the gas field in
northeastern Bangladesh, the prime minister also urged the local
people to face the situation with courage and patience.
</P>
<P>
The fire, caused by a massive explosion during drilling by the
U.S. company Occidental, has engulfed the gas field and scorched
the nearby trees, houses and rail tracts besides creating panic
among the local residents.
</P>
<P>
The fire is still out of control but the height of flame has
showed some reduction.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister gave on-the-spot instructions to the
concerned authorities to accelerate the efforts to bring the
situation to normal.
</P>
<P>
Terming the blaze as a "major accident," she however asked a
gathering of local people not to be worried about it. "We are with
you, everything is being done to cope with the situation," she
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
