<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Desertification Threats Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A representative from the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP) said today that
desertification is threatening nearly 70 percent of Ethiopia's
land.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting held to commemorate the World
Desertification Day here, Christian Lehembre said Ethiopia is one
of the countries in which desertification threatens the lives of
millions of people and constrains the ability of the country to
develop a healthy agricultural and natural resources base.
</P>
<P>
Lehembre said drought is another major problem in Ethiopia
and recurs every 7-8 years causing famine and loss of human and
animal lives.
</P>
<P>
There is sufficient evidence that the highest incidence of
poverty occurs in drylands, he said, adding that the world day to
combat desertification is an opportune occasion to call for and
encourage the work that is required on a sustained basis at many
levels.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, General Manager of Environmental
Protection Authority of Ethiopia Tewolde Berhan Gebre-Egziabher said
Ethiopia has already approved a countrywide conservation strategy
whose main focus is combating land degradation.
</P>
<P>
He said a national steering committee has been created consisting
of representatives of the Environmental Protection Authority, several
relevant ministries, non-governmental organizations, higher
educational and research institutions.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics available, about 900 million people
across the world suffer from desertification related problems, of
whom 80 percent live in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
In Africa, one third of the population suffers from this
problem, while three fourth of the people of the member countries
of the Inter-Governmental Authority on Development (IGAD) are
facing the problem.
</P>
<P>
The World Desertification Day was established following the
agreement on the United Nations convention to combat
desertification in 1994. enditem

=06171447

=06171506
NNNN
22:53 22:53 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
