<HEADLINE> International Economic Cooperation Fair Opens in Shenyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 300 Chinese and foreign
businessmen will discuss issues related to economic and
technological cooperation during an international trade fair that
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The '97 International Economic and Technological Cooperation
Fair aims to attract more investments for the Shenyang Economic
and Technological Development Zone, said an official of the zone's
administration department.
</P>
<P>
The zone was established in the capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province in 1988. So far, businessmen from 33 countries
and regions have made a total of 2.48 billion US dollars in
contracted investment in 552 projects.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, these projects are expected to create 39.8
billion yuan (4.8 billion US dollars) in output value, and earn
9.8 billion yuan (1.1 billion US dollars) in pre-tax profits and
920 million US dollars of foreign exchange through export. 
</P>
</TEXT>
