<HEADLINE> Thailand to Sign Cultural Pact With Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is ready to sign an
agreement on cultural cooperation with Cambodia to promote
understanding and relationship between the peoples of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet approved the draft pact to be signed with
Cambodia at its weekly meeting today, according to a press release
from the Thai Government House.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be signed by the Thai Foreign Ministry and
the Cambodian Ministry of Culture and Arts on June 21 this year
when Thai Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh visits Cambodia.
</P>
