<HEADLINE> 2 Soldiers Killed in Rebel Attack in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Two soldiers were killed and five
others wounded today in a clash between the Philippine government
forces and Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels in the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Citing a military report, the Philippine Television reported
that the clash took place this morning in Carmen Town, North
Cotabato Province, in central Mindanao when a group of rebels
attacked an army patrol.
</P>
<P>
The military expected a higher casualty number on the rebel
side and additional troops have been rushed to Carmen and other
parts of the province, the television report said.
</P>
<P>
The MILF is a breakaway faction of the former larger Muslim
rebel group, the Moro National Liberation Front (MNLF), which
already signed a peace deal with the government last September.
</P>
<P>
The government has been seeking to forge a similar deal with
the MILF, which is currently the strongest anti-government group
in the country, with an estimated membership of 12,000.
</P>
<P>
The two sides began their initial peace talks early this year,
but the peace process has been stalled because of sporadic
fighting between the two sides.  
</P>
</TEXT>
