<HEADLINE> 72 Die of AIDS in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The deadly AIDS has so far
claimed 72 lives in the Himalayan kingdom of Nepal.
</P>
<P>
A total of 647 people, including 364 men and 283 women, have
tested HIV positive, which means they are carrying in their blood
the deadly virus causing AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The National AIDS Control Center said today that 234 women
engaged in sex trade and 36 housewives have tested HIV positive.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures show that AIDS has been sexually transmitted
to 351 men and 11 women while 12 drug addicts are found to have
contracted the disease through the use of syringes.
</P>
<P>
Two babies born of mother already infected with the AIDS virus
have also tested HIV positive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
