<HEADLINE> Art Exhibition on HK Return Held by Central Departments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- An art exhibition organized by the
central Party and government departments to greet the return of
Hong Kong opened here today at the China National Art Museum.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee and
vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, attended the
opening ceremony and offered the inscription "Wash Away Shame and
Humiliation of 100 Years, Usher in Development and Prosperity
Generation after Generation."
</P>
<P>
Vice-President Rong Yiren also wrote lines for the
occasion. Ding Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee, viewed the show.
</P>
<P>
The 280 paintings and calligraphy works were selected from more
than 600 entries by staff members of the central party and
government departments. Thirty-six of the painters and
calligraphers were ministerial level officials. Works of many
prestigious Chinese are also on display at the museum.
</P>
<P>
The works highlight the Chinese tradition of resisting imperial
invasions and the landmark successes made by the people under the
CPC leadership. 
</P>
