<HEADLINE> Meeting between Russian, EU Leaders Canceled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Boris Nemtsov, Russia's First
Deputy Prime Minister, today canceled a scheduled meeting with
Leon Brittan, Vice-president of the Commission of the European
Union, to protest the EU's discriminative trade policy against
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Brittan, who is on a visit to Russia, reiterated the EU's
position to list Russia as a country that has not adopted a
market-oriented economy, when he had talks with Russian officials
in Moscow, Nemtsov's press secretary said.
</P>
<P>
The EU commission has recently decided to levy a 32.9 percent
interim anti-dumping surcharge on the seamless steel tubes
exported by Russia to some EU member states. The decision has
caused a great loss to Russia.
</P>
<P>
So far, the EU commission has levied anti-dumping taxes on 14
kinds of Russian goods including seamless steel tubes, potash
fertilizer and manganese. 
</P>
