<HEADLINE> Iran's Parliament Attacks US Congress Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Parliament Speaker Ali
Akbar Nateq-Nouri today termed the recent U.S. Congress resolution
recognizing Jerusalem as Israel's capital as "a scandal and a
conspiracy against Islamic states."
</P>
<P>
The hardline speaker made the remarks at a meeting with
members of the central council of the Association of the Islamic
Coalition, the state-run Tehran Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
On June 10, the U.S. Congress voted 406 for and 17 against, to
transfer the U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem. The
Congress also adopted a decision recognizing Jerusalem as
Israel's "undivided capital."
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Congress move, though non-binding, has in the past
week invited condemnation by Iranian officials and local press, as
well as by the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani Sunday told
reporters that the U.S. Congress resolution showed that the
U.S. did not care about Muslims.
</P>
<P>
"Introducing Qods (Jerusalem) as the capital of the Israeli
regime is a sign of snubbing the Muslim world and shows the unjust
positions of the United States," Rafsanjani said.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Propagation Organization, the Association for the
Defense of Values of the Islamic Revolution and the Council on
Coordination of Islamic Propagation Monday issued statements
calling on Iranians to take part in anti-U.S. demonstrations
this Friday to protest against the U.S. Congress resolution.
</P>
