<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Market Gains 62.23 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 62.23 points to
4087.64 as against yesterday's close of 4025.41.
</P>
<P>
The National Index also shot up by 23.66 points to 1748.93 from
1725.27 previously.
</P>
<P>
The BSE market today made a recovery again after yesterday's
hesitancy with several front-line shares scoring impressive gains
in hectic activity on heavy speculative support and continued
purchases by foreign institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
Great Eastern Shipping recorded a sharp upswing on brisk buying
prompted by news that the company has recommended 30-percent
dividend following excellent performance in 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
While some brokers attributed the buoyancy to the deferment of
a decision on the contentious issue of a hike in prices of
petroleum products till June 27, a few others said the market
would have witnessed a firm trend even the government had
announced the gas price hike Monday.
</P>
