<HEADLINE> Soeharto: Biotechnology Gives Solutions to Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto said
today that solutions have been found to a number of problems
confronting the human race since biotechnology emerged in the
sphere of science.
</P>
<P>
"Biotechnology has provided solutions to problems like genetic
diseases, environmental pollution, destruction of biodiversity,
starvation and energy crisis," Soeharto said when opening a
biotechnology conference at the state palace.
</P>
<P>
He said history clearly points out how the human race has made
incredible progress through science and technology, particularly
in the field of biotechnology.
</P>
<P>
But Soeharto added that although biotechnology provides
solutions to a number of problems, it can also cause disasters
when improperly implemented.
</P>
<P>
He called on the developing countries including Indonesia to
use science and technology to achieve people's prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"Nowadays, however, we can see there is a wide gap between the
developing countries and the industrial states, which can control
modern technology," he said.
</P>
<P>
If such a gap could not be overcome, human beings will always
be subjected to unfair situations, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that developing countries should keep on narrowing
the gap using science and technology, through the United Nations
and other international and regional forums.
</P>
<P>
Some 500 local and 87 foreign experts from 16 countries or
regions are attending the conference which will last until June
19.
</P>
<P>
The head of the conference's organizer, Asril Darussamin, said
the meeting provides opportunity to experts to present their
findings and exchange information on the field of biotechnology.
</P>
</TEXT>
