<HEADLINE> Australia Beats Solomon Islands in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 17 (Reuter) - Australia overwhelmed Solomon
Islands 6-2 (halftime 3-1) in a World Cup Oceania Zone Group One
qualifying match at Parramatta Stadium in Sydney, Australia, on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Robbie Slater opened the scoring for Australia in the 16th
minute and one minute later his teammate Graham Arnold added
another.
</P>
<P>
Solomon Islands pulled one back through Augustine Peli, who
netted in the 29th minute before Jimmy Kaierea made a mistake to
score an own goal while thwarting an Australian attack in the 39th
minute.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Australia's Ernie Tapai scored a hat-trick
by netting in 48th and 52nd minute respecit, while Aurelio Vidmar
completed the mauling by converting a penalty kick in the 75th
minute.
</P>
<P>
The other Solomon Islands' goal came from Batram Suri in the
66th minute.
</P>
<P>
Australia will face Tahiti in its next match in Sydney on June
19.
