<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Basic Law is Creative Law  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The formulation and promulgation of the Basic Law is of
historical importance. It has legalized the great concept of the
"one country, two systems", defined the basic system and basic
policies of the Hong Kong SAR and drawn a clear blueprint for
future Hong Kong. It serves as a fundamental legal guarantee for
the long-term stability and prosperity of Hong Kong, and is in the
fundamental interest of the entire Chinese people including the
Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
The late leader Deng Xiaoping highly praised the drafting of
the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR, describing it as a law of
historical and international significance.
</P>
<P>
As for its historical significance, the Basic Law involves the
past, the present and the future. As for its international
significance, it is of long-term significance to not only the
third world, but also the entire mankind. It is a creative
masterpiece, he said.
</P>
<P>
At that time, the public opinions agreed that it was rare in
history that a county devoted such an enormous amount of manpower,
materials and funds to the careful formulation process of the
basic law.
</P>
<P>
For this reason, since its promulgation, the Basic Law has been
well received by all Hong Kong compatriots, and has won favorable
comments from the international community as well.
</P>
<P>
The drafting and formulating the Basic Law is a democratic
process, as can be seen from the composition of the drafting
committee. Of the committee's 59 members, 23, or well over one
third, were Hong Kong residents.
</P>
<P>
According to the stipulations, each article of the Basic Law is
subject to passing by a vote of two thirds of all committee
members. Should an article fail to be passed by a two-thirds
majority, it is subject to passing by a two-thirds majority after
being revised.
</P>
<P>
Every drafting committee member cast a total of 164 votes on
the foreword, 160 articles and the three appendixes of the Basic
Law. This is rare in the legislation of any other country.
</P>
<P>
The process of drafting and formulating the Basic Law is also a
successful practice in which the Hong Kong people became involved
in Hong Kong's transition. In the course of drafting the Basic
Law, the drafting committee held nine plenary meetings and
conducted two large-scale consulting activities in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Drafting committee members made 100 revisions of the draft
Basic Law. Half of the revisions were based on opinions expressed
by the Hong Kong residents and the opinions were collected by the
Consultancy Committee.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan, director of the Hong Kong Branch of the Xinhua News
Agency, said, "The drafting of the Basic Law made a good beginning
for the Hong Kong people to participate in regional affairs."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meteorological Satellite Finds its Position in Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists this morning
succeeded in positioning the Fengyun 2, a meteorological satellite
launched on June 10, over the equator at 105 degrees east
longitude.
</P>
<P>
Fengyun 2 will start its assigned mission after a period of
orbital examination and debugging.
</P>
<P>
The successful positioning at 10:20 Beijing time and future
operations of the satellite mark a milestone in China's
meteorological modernization drive, sources from the China
Aerospace Corporation (CAC) said.
</P>
<P>
The overall performance of Fengyun 2 has reached the
technological requirements set for satellites of its kind
developed in the 1990s, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The Xi'an Satellite Control Center, a CAC test team and marine
surveying ships have been tracking and controlling the satellite
for one week to ensure its proper positioning.
</P>
<P>
Fengyun 2 is the first meteorological satellite developed by
China that is in synchronous orbit with the earth. Covering about
100 million square kilometers of earth surface with China in the
central location, Fengyun 2 can provide meteorological information
such as cloud maps, temperatures, and wind movements over China
and its neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Weighing 1.38 tons, Fengyun 2 is equipped with a scanning
radiometer, a cloud coverage information system, and a data
collection translator. It will help improve medium- and long-term
weather forecasts and those for natural disasters in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
