<HEADLINE> 25 Killed in Ambush by MTA Splinter Group in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five civilians were killed
and five others wounded in an ambush last Friday laid by a
break-away group of the Khun Sa-led Mong Tai Army (MTA), a former
drug trafficking armed group in Myanmar, official sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
Forty members of the MTA splinter faction, led by Khay Ngim,
ambushed a civilian convoy in Myanmar's eastern Shan state near
Tachilek, they said.
</P>
<P>
Khun Sa and the majority of his MTA have unconditionally
surrendered to the Myanmar government in succession since January
1995, bringing the number of the surrendered to 14,949 by the end
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
There is still a handful of people from the MTA splinter group
who have not yet laid down their arms to the government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
