<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tribute to Deng Xiaoping's Contribution To Hong Kong's Return -- Xinhua Commentary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- As China's resumption of its
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong approaches, the Chinese
people are filled with joy and inspiration in erasing the traces
of the 150-year disgrace.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, all countries around the world are following
the event closely. The smooth return is based on Deng Xiaoping's
"one country, two systems" principle, his concept for solving the
Hong Kong and Taiwan issues.
</P>
<P>
It was Deng who led the push for Hong Kong's return with
revolutionary courage and a realistic approach. Showing his deep
affection for Hong Kong, he said he wanted to live until 1997
so that he could see with his own eyes China's recovery of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Today, as the time approaches, we hail all the more this great
man of the 20th century and his legacy in Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
That return has followed a difficult and tortuous course. The
people of China never gave up its sovereignty over Hong Kong for
the past 150 years and more, and never recognized the unequal
treaties imposed by the imperialists and colonialists.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people have always regarded the imperialists'
occupation of Hong Kong by force as an enormous national
humiliation and they have firmly be convinced that Hong Kong would
return to the motherland.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
