<HEADLINE> Senior Legislator Stresses Economic Growth in Inspection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese legislator has
said that to boldly develop the economy and greatly improve the
people's life are a "magic weapon" for administering our nation
and making it stronger.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, made the remarks during an inspection
tour in central China's Hunan Province from June 15-17.
</P>
<P>
At this critical time with the turn of the century in sight,
"it is quite necessary for us to further broaden our minds, be
bolder in work and advance at a faster pace" to deepen the
country's reform and opening-up, he said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the reform of state-owned enterprises, local
officials should go all out to boost the growth of share-holding
companies, non-state businesses, foreign-funded ventures and
tourism, he noted.
</P>
<P>
To carry forward the Communist Party's fundamental policies
for rural areas is key to the country's long-term stability, he
said, adding that in particular, the household contract system
will remain unchanged.  
</P>
