<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tribute to Deng Xiaoping's Contribution to Hong Kong's Return -- Xinhua Commentary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Before the founding of New China, the return of Hong Kong was
only a national dream. Since the People's Republic of China was
founded, the Chinese government has repeatedly stated that it
would solve the Hong Kong issue at the right moment, but the issue
was repeatedly delayed because the time was not ripe both
internally and externally.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, with the stable political situation and a thriving
economy, Deng Xiaoping made the bold decision to take back Hong
Kong in keeping with the nation's aspirations.
</P>
<P>
In 1982, in a meeting with Britain's Prime Minister, Margaret
Thatcher, he firmly stated that in 1997 China would take Hong Kong
back and then pointed out: "It was under this premise that China
and Britain have started negotiations on ways and methods to solve
the Hong Kong issue."
</P>
<P>
Should China and Britain fail to reach accord, he said, "China
will reconsider the time and way to take Hong Kong back."
</P>
<P>
Today, we are deeply moved by Deng Xiaoping's patriotic
compassion and his firm stand on safeguarding China's sovereignty
and dignity as we are reviewing his remarks. Comrade Deng Xiaoping
was indeed a most ardent patriot and firmest national hero who
safeguarded our country's interests.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tribute to Deng Xiaoping's Contribution to Hong Kong's Return -- Xinhua Commentary (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"It is the Chinese nation's common aspiration to reunify the
motherland and it was a great invention of Comrade Deng Xiaoping
when he introduced the 'one country, two systems' concept for
peaceful reunification." Party General Secretary Jiang Zemin said
this in his speech at the memorial service for Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the Communist Party's experience, Deng Xiaoping
came up with this concept to solve the Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao
issues. It is an important part of his theory on building
socialism with Chinese characteristics and has far-reaching
importance in solving similar historical problems in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
According to the concept, China will practise socialism on the
major part of the country while allowing Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan to maintain their capitalist system for a long time.
</P>
<P>
Deng pointed out that this was developed in view of the reality
of both the historical and present situations for the purpose of
maintaining prosperity and stability in Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan and peacefully resolving the reunification of the
motherland in a peaceful and reasonable way that can be acceptable
to all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
In developing this concept, Deng set a fine example in solving
practical problems with dialectical materialism and historical
materialism. As he himself repeatedly said, this concept provided
a way of solving other conflicts existing in the world.
</P>
<P>
Therefore his invention is not only a monumental contribution
to the great cause of the reunification of the Chinese nation but
also represents his strategic thinking for solving remaining
historical problems and maintaining peace and stability around the
globe.
</P>
<P>
It is also a major contribution to humanity made by a great
statesman who loved peace and was deeply-concerned about human
destiny.
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
