<HEADLINE> Ghana Beats Ireland 2-1 in World Youth Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALOR SETAR, Malaysia, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Ghana defeated
Ireland 2-1 in a group C match of the world youth soccer
championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ghana's Bashiru Gambo scored the opening goal in 28th minute
but Trevor Molloy of Ireland levelled the score seven minutes
after the break.
</P>
<P>
Ghana's Mohamed-Kamil Mouktar netted the winning goal in the
67th minute with a deft placement.
</P>
<P>
Ghana, runners-up to Brazil in the 1993 championships of the
under-20 tournament in Australia, will meet China next on
Thursday. Ireland takes on the United States the same day.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Asian champions South Korea and South Africa, the
African runners-up, played a goalless draw in the first group B
match at Kuching.
</P>
<P>
Both teams now face tougher opponents in Brazil and France, who
clash later on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Two top teams and four best third-place finishers from the six
groups will qualify for the knock-out rounds. The final will be
played on July 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
