<HEADLINE> German Prosecutors Drop Appeal in Graf Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- German prosecutors on Tuesday had
dropped an appeal against the verdict for the father of German
tennis star Steffi Graf for tax evasion.
</P>
<P>
"Mannheim prosecutors have withdrawn their appeal against the
verdict of the Mannheim court in the case against Peter Graf,"
prosecutors said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
They said his defence lawyers also announced the withdrawal of
their legal measure.
</P>
<P>
This means that the 45-month sentence imposed on him was now
legally binding.
</P>
<P>
Peter Graf was convicted on six counts of actual and attempted
tax evasion on Steffi's earnings and had since been waiting for
the result of the appeals process.
</P>
<P>
Graf has already served 15 months in investigative custody
during the investigation and subsequent trial. 
</P>
