<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Delta to Form Economic Community </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen powerful Chinese cities
in the Yangtze River Delta area have joined together to form a
highly competitive economic community to prepare for the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
The cities, including Shanghai, Nanjing, Hangzhou, Wuxi,
Ningbo, Suzhou, and Changzhou, established an economic
coordinating association in May in Yangzhou city, in Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The mayors of these cities have agreed to increase regional
cooperation in tourism, the building of chain-stores, and economic
integration over the next two years.
</P>
<P>
The 15 cities generated a GDP of more than one trillion yuan
last year, a sixth of the nation's total. That figure is expected
to rise to over two trillion yuan by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
As the country's most developed area, the 15-city economic belt
has attracted more than half the world's 500 largest
multinationals and provides more than 20 percent of China's
exports.
</P>
<P>
For mutual benefits, these city governments are making an
effort to eliminate various administrative barriers and economic
limitations between each other to improve resource distribution
and flow of key production elements.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Able to Manage HK Well: Shi Hian Chen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Shi Hian Chen, vice chairman of
the Chinese Culture Promotion Society in Thailand, has expressed
the belief that the Chinese government will unswervingly implement
the principles and policies initiated by the late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping on Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chen, a Chinese-Thai, who is also president of Thailand's
Chinese Journalists Welfare Association, said Hong Kong will
certainly be better tomorrow, when Deng's principles of "one
China, two systems," high degree of autonomy for Hong Kong and
Hong Kong's existing systems remaining unchanged for 50 years are
carried out.
</P>
<P>
"With the concerted endeavors of the entire Chinese nation,
Hong Kong will be administered well, letting those who have this
or that kind of misgivings at the moment be fully convinced," he
said in a recent exclusive interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong can play an exemplary role, he noted, adding that if
Hong Kong is well administered, it will have a great, positive
impact on Taiwan's reunification with the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He said the overwhelming majority of the people of Chinese
origin are overjoyed at Hong Kong's return, regarding it as a
giant laudable step toward China's eventual unification.  
</P>
</TEXT>
