<HEADLINE> Taiwanese Securities Companies Confident in HK Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Taiwanese securities brokers in
Hong Kong tell the local media that they are full of confidence in
business prospects in Hong Kong after it returns to the embrace of
the motherland on July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
Referring to concern over whether or not Taiwanese securities
companies in Hong Kong will be treated fairly after July 1,
Stanley Lai, head of the Taiwan Securities (HK) Co. Ltd., said he
is confident in Hong Kong's future and expects that Taiwanese
securities companies will receive fair treatment.
</P>
<P>
Nelson Lip, head of the Masterlink Securities (HK) Corp. Ltd.,
expresses the same opinion, adding, "Transactions handled by
Masterlink have not declined but recorded a sustained growth in
recent months."
</P>
<P>
The company has recently set up a branch in Shanghai to expand
business on the Chinese mainland and develop underwriting business
for local companies to be listed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that in recent months an increasing number of
Taiwan-based securities companies have come to Hong Kong to engage
in the underwriting business, leading to fiercer competition among
themselves and with other brokerage houses.
</P>
<P>
Gilbert Hwang, managing director of the Taiwan International
Securities Ltd., says Hong Kong will maintain its status as an
international financial center.
</P>
<P>
While continuing to develop in Hong Kong, he says, his company
will open a representative office in Beijing and Shanghai
respectively in the near future and expand regional operations via
Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
