<HEADLINE> Indian Airlines to Sell, Lease Entire Fleet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indian Airlines (IA) has
decided to sell and lease its entire fleet of 12 Boeing 737-200s
in a bid to ease its tight financial position, IA sources said
here today.
</P>
<P>
It expected to get 70 million U.S. dollars by selling its
entire fleet of 12 Boeing 737-200s and will take the same aircraft
on lease from buyers. Global tenders for the sale and lease back
of the aircraft which are on average 12 years old will be shortly
floated in an exercise undertaken for the first time by the
state-owned airline to mobilize badly needed resources. The tender
closes on August 12.
</P>
<P>
There will be no disruption of operations even for a single day
because the aircraft will continue to be with the airlines though
in the capacity as a leasee and not as an owner, the same sources
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
