<HEADLINE> Rebels Ambush Bus in Northern Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Lord's Resistance Army
(LRA) ambushed a bus at Brogali in northern Uganda Monday, killing
one passenger and injuring eight other people.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today said, the rebels shot at the
speeding bus before spraying it with small arms' fire and the bus
driver however drove through the ambush amid the gunfire.
</P>
<P>
The bus carrying over 50 passengers was travelling from Kitgum,
Uganda's northern city to Kampala, the capital, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
LRA led by Joseph Konny started its war against Uganda's central
government in northern part of the country in 1987 and is still
destabilising the east African country. 
