<HEADLINE> Foreign-Funded Sector Grows 23 Percent in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 17 (xinhua) -- The foreign-invested sector in
vietnam grew by 22.8 percent in the first five months of this
year, said the latest issue of the Vietnam Investment Review.
</P>
<P>
However, the domestic industrial growth was "more humble," one
percentage point lower than last year's 11.9 percent, the
english-language weekly said.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed slower industrial growth to insufficient
investments in various sectors while a handful of domestic
industrial enterprises incur great debts.
</P>
<P>
The review added that outdated and backward technology also
drags on industrial productivity.
</P>
<P>
In addition, industries also suffered from the slump in prices
in the past three months. Increased industrial production has
resulted in production exceeding demand, prompting last year's
high trade deficit.
</P>
<P>
Experts agreed that in order to give fresh impetus to their
development, the domestic industries must strengthen their own
financial power and operational effectiveness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
