<HEADLINE> Nigerian Civil Servants On Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Civil Servants in northern Nigeria's
Kaduna State went on an indefinite strike on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Local media reported today that all the state ministries were
deserted on Monday, as the workers were all staying home.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the authorities had deployed fully-armed anti-riot
policemen at the state secretariat from early morning in
anticipation of violence, but later reduced the number of policemen.
</P>
<P>
The State Public Service Negotiating Council warned the government
of the strike on Friday, after all other means have failed to persuade
the government to pay arrears of promised allowances for medical,
transport and accommodation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
