<HEADLINE> hkhk-Appointment of HKSAR Provisional District Organizations Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Hong Kong, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The appointment of all existing
members of Hong Kong's district organizations to the provisional
district organizations of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) is widely acclaimed here as good for maintaining the
stability and prosperity of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with a decision announced by the Office of the
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong SAR, all existing members of the
Urban Council, the Regional Council and the 18 District Boards
will continue to serve in the Provisional Urban Council, the
Provisional Regional Council and the Provisional District Boards,
while 116 new appointed seats were added.
</P>
<P>
Ngai Shiu-kit, a member of the Preparatory Committee of Hong
Kong SAR, said that the additional appointment of a large number
of professionals and personalities with rich experiences in
regional affairs to the provisional regional organizations
embodies the principle of a balanced participation.
</P>
<P>
While the full participation of the existing members in the
provisional organizations facilitates the maintenance of social
stability, the additional appointments which have drawn people
from all walks of life are in the interests of all social strata,
noted Lee Lin Sang, a deputy to the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The decision to retain all the existing members while adding new
appointments epitomizes the spirit of tolerance, observed Sze Chi
Ching, a member of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Daniel W.K. Lam, chairman of the Hong Kong Regional
Council, noted that from the list of appointment, professional
appointees have made up the bulk of the organizations and many of
them have work experience in the district and regional boards and
the Urban Council. This will be conducive to the operation of the
provisional district organizations, Lam said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
