<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Former U.S. Secretary of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
met with former U.S. Secretary of State Henry Kissinger at
Zhongnanhai here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said he was pleased to meet Dr. Kissinger and expressed his
appreciation of Kissinger's penetrating insight and judgement
which he upheld on the discussion of the MFN issue.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger said he was happy to visit China again. He said he
had spent wonderful days in Beijing and sincerely hoped that
U.S.-Chinese relations would continue to improve.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign
Affairs Office of the State Council, and Mei Zhaorong, president
of the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs. 
</P>
