<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices reversed their
downward trend and started to rise on the Singapore market with
the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index gaining 13.18 points
to close at 2,004.26 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 88.64 million units, valued
at 277.68 million Singapore dollars (about 194.18 million US
dollars). Declines still led advances by 158 to 143, while 326
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Westmont Land was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 3.71 million units. It was followed by the Development
Bank of Singapore (DBS) Land which had 2.82 million shares traded.
The Overseas Union Bank (OUB) Right was next with 2.815 million
units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 2.1 Singapore dollars to finish at 24.2
dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign increased by
one dollar to end at 28.6 Singapore dollars. NBT closed 80 cents
higher at 20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, OUE, Samanda Holdings, and the Thai Prime Fund
declined by 30 cents each to end at 6.65 Singapore dollars, 10.4
Singapore dollars, and 8.4 US dollars respectively. Tech Resources
Industry fell by 29 cents to close at 2.61 dollars, while Parkway
was 25 cents lower at 6.35 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
