<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Haikou to Enhance Cooperation with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The mayor of Haikou, the capital of
China's southernmost province, Hainan, says that Hong Kong's
return on July 1 will bring more opportunities for economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen have invested a total of 1.75 billion US
dollars in Haikou in the past few years, accounting for half of
the city's overseas investment, Mayor Zeng Haorong says. Overseas
investment in the city has reached about 3.4 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong investors have become extensively involved in the
local economy, investing in local industrial, agricultural, real
estate, and tourist projects, and in infrastructure," he says.
</P>
<P>
There are 3,650 ventures in the city funded by Hong Kong
businessmen, and nearly 60 percent of the city's exports go
through Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Both Hong Kong and Haikou have benefited a lot from this
economic cooperation, and Hong Kong businessmen have good returns
on their revestments," Zeng says.
</P>
<P>
According to the city's Ninth Five-Year Plan, it will
concentrate on developing high-tech, high value-added,
highly-profitable industries, and the tourist industry to make it
an international tropical tourist city.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong will 'mirror' Haikou's economic growth, which has
similar economic opportunities as Hong Kong 30 year ago, and the
return will help speed up development of the local investment and
finance business," Zeng notes.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong can also channel more overseas economic information
into Haikou, and help improve the local information industry, he
says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
