<HEADLINE> hkhk--JLG Reaches Agreement on Multilateral Treaties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese and British sides of
the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) have reached agreement
on the mechanism for the continued application of multilateral
treaties in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
from July 1 1997 on.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese side of the JLG, the two sides have
also reached agreement on the script of Notes of legal and
diplomatic actions intended to ensure the application of the
treaties in the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
At present, the two sides are in the process of issuing the
Notes to international treaty depositories as well as the United
Nations Secretary-General. 
</P>
