<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The member states of the European Union (EU) finally reached
an agreement Monday in Amsterdam to adopt the budgetary Stability
Pact, completed by a resolution on employment. This compromise
avoided a major crisis over the future European single currency.
France has obtained a text which insists on the need to better
coordinate policies by EU countries to better fight unemployment.
</P>
<P>
-- The meeting of mediation on the crisis in Congo Republic ended
in a total failure Monday in Gabonese capital Libreville. The
mediation committee headed by Gabonese President Omar Bongo said
that it ``has not succeeded for the moment in deciding between the
parties concerned with a view to put an end to the crisis.''
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The finance ministers of the European Union member states
reached an agreement upon the budgetary Stability Pact for the
future European single currency, which constrains single currency
members with rigid budget control and aims to punish those countries
which trespass. The pact is completed by a part on employment as
was required by France.
</P>
<P>
-- A tempest with exceptional violence struck last evening the
Seine-Maritime region in northern France. A mother and her two
children were killed by mudslide when they were leaving their
vehicle in La Vaupaliere near Rouen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
