<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Has 1,230 Overseas-Backed Agricultural Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investors have started more
than 1,230 agricultural projects in the province of Shandong in
east China, accounting for 6.6 percent of the province's total
number of overseas-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, contracts on these projects
involve 112 million U.S. dollars of overseas funds, 4.5 percent of
the province's total.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is a leading agricultural producer in China and has
been ranked high in the production of grain, cotton, edible oil
and vegetables. Plentiful resources have created a lot of
opportunities for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Many of the overseas-backed enterprises are engaged in farm
processing business. They delivered 1.54 billion yuan worth of
processed farmed produce for exports in 1996, accounting for 14
percent of the province's total exports for the year.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the inflow of overseas investment into
the province's agricultural sector has not only brought in a big
number of improved varieties of agricultural products and advanced
technologies, but also advanced the industrialization of the
province's agriculture and urbanization in the province's rural
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
