<HEADLINE> Container Transport Record on Continental Bridge Created </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIANYUNGANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese seaport at the
eastern end of the new Eurasian continental bridge reported a
monthly record in container handling in May.
</P>
<P>
Lianyungang in Jiangsu Province handled more than 4,000 TEUs
last month, bringing the total for the first five months of this
year to 16,570 TEUs, a ten-fold increase over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The continental bridge stretches 10,900 kilometers from
Lianyungang to Rotterdam in the Netherlands, with a rail link
passing through over 40 countries and regions and connecting the
Pacific Ocean with the Atlantic Ocean.
</P>
<P>
The city of Lianyungang has placed great importance on
promoting international trade via the line. On April 1 of this
year, a special cargo train left the city to Altay in the Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region of northwest China. Local rail
departments, ports, and customs offices joined hands to ensure
fast and safe transportation of the goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
