<HEADLINE> Chinese Highway Company Expands Rapidly With H Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Anhui Expressway Co. Ltd, the
first expressway company to list its shares on the Hong Kong stock
exchange, has become one of the best-performers on Hong Kong's H
share market, with profits growing more than 50 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The company saw its business almost double 1995's figure, going
to 164 million yuan, and net income climbed to 90.47 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
When it listed its shares in Hong Kong last November it raised
888 million yuan, allowing it to build or purchase more highways
and expressways, Wang Shui, the chairman of the board, told the
first annual meeting of shareholders.
</P>
<P>
The company now plans to spend 550 million yuan building an
expressway linking Shanghai with the southwestern city of
Chengdu. It also plans to purchase more highways and to play an
important role in the economic development of Anhui and central
and western provinces, according to the company's board chairman.
</P>
</TEXT>
