<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Hong Kong Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition entitled the
History and Development of Hong Kong opened here today at the
Birendra International Conference Center to mark Hong Kong's
upcoming return to China.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the exhibition sponsored by
the Chinese Embassy in Nepal, Chinese ambassador Zhang Jiuhuan
said Hong Kong will return to the embrace of the motherland in 13
days. This great event is drawing much attention of the whole
world not only because it is a return after 150 years, or a return
realized in a peaceful manner, but also because it is a return
realized out of the concept of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that under the guidance of the great concept of late
Deng Xiaoping, a great man of this century, the Chinese government
will carry out in Hong Kong, after its return to the motherland,
special policies unprecedented both in China and in the world at
large, the basic content of which can be summarized as "one
country, two systems, " "rule of Hong Kong by Hong Kong people"
and "a high degree of autonomy."
</P>
<P>
The above-mentioned policies guarantees the stable transfer of
Hong Kong, said Zhang, adding that it is predictable that after
its return, Hong Kong will continue to enjoy stability and
prosperity, and will have a better future.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Finance Minister Rabindra Nath Sharma took part in the
opening ceremony on behalf of Prime Minister Chand.
</P>
<P>
He said the resumption of the exercise of its sovereignty by
China over Hong Kong from July 1, 1997 will be a great event of
national pride and dignity for China and its people.
</P>
<P>
About 200 people attended the opening ceremony of the
exhibition, which will last a week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
