<HEADLINE> Baoding-Tianjin Expressway Being Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Second-phase construction has
started on a 140-km-long expressway from Baoding, in north China's
Hebei province, to Tianjin, the largest port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
In Xiongxian county of Hebei, piers are being built for a
bridge with a length of 1,800 meters, over a tributary of the
Haihe river. It is regarded as the most difficult part of the
expressway.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will be linked with the Beijing-Shenzhen
super-highway in the west, and another expressway from Tianjin,
via Shanhaiguan, to northeast China, in the east.
</P>
<P>
It will also be a major road for Tianjin to reach the capitals
of Hebei, Henan, and Shanxi.
</P>
<P>
Construction work for the four-lane expressway will be
completed by 1998. First-phase construction began in March last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Hebei section of the expressway is 105 km long, costing an
investment of 1.9 billion yuan. There are now five expressways
being built in the province, with a combined length of nearly 800
km.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is also building four expressways totaling about 140 km
long, sources say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
