<HEADLINE> China Encourages Housing Cooperatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China now has more than 5,000
housing cooperatives since the first such body was established in
Shanghai in 1986.
</P>
<P>
This information was provided at a recent training class on the
management of apartments built by housing cooperatives held in
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the training class, Li Zhendong, Vice Minister of
Construction, said that building flats by housing cooperatives
conforms with reform requirements, people's actual income standard
and their demand for a more comfortable living condition, and
should be practised in more large cities since successful
experience has been gained from practices in some medium-sized and
small cities, as well as in county seats.
</P>
<P>
To solve housing difficulties, moderate and low wage earners in
some cities and towns have voluntarily formed housing cooperatives
and paid a certain amount of money in advance to repay investment
for construction of apartments, which will be distributed among
members of housing cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
This has gone in tandem with the "comfortable living" project
launched by the central government and aimed at providing flats to
workers with low income in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Over the past years, flats with a total floor space of 70
million sq m have been constructed under the "comfortable living"
project, using 25 billion yuan in loans from state-owned banks.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 people from across the country attended the
training class, sponsored by the China Council for the Promotion
of Housing Cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
Participants studied relevant stipulations on cooperative
housing, management of properties and experiences in this regard
from a number of cities including Shanghai, Tianjin, Wuhan and
Nanjing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
