<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets Up First Community College </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The first community college in
Shanghai, China's leading metropolis, has been set up in Xuhui
district.
</P>
<P>
The college is run by social sectors with assistance from the
local government. It observes the responsibility system under the
board of trustees.
</P>
<P>
Chen Quanfu, former Dean of a faculty of the Shanghai Jiaotong
(communications) University, is president of the new Guangqi
College, which is named after Xu Guangqi, a reformist of the Ming
Dynasty and a renowned scientist.
</P>
<P>
The college now has four majors, including real estate and
business management. It plans to enroll 280 students this
fall. 
</P>
