<HEADLINE> Discipline Inspection Groups to Check Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, June 17 (Xinhua) -- With the determination to help
build a clean and efficient government, the Chinese Communist
Party's Central Commission for Discipline Inspection will send
work group across the country to supervise anti-corruption
operations.
</P>
<P>
The central task of the inspection groups is to check the fight
against extravagant acts in some government establishments while
promote a thrift and honest work style. Extravagancy includes
spending lavishly on meetings and ceremonies, using public funds
for private housing decorations and buying mobile-phones.
</P>
<P>
The groups will go to selected provinces and cities as well as
central government departments and commissions in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee issued in March this year a set of
rules asking Party officials and members to guard against
corruptive activities. The document will be used as the main
guideline for the coming inspections.
</P>
<P>
The check will start first among leading officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
