<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Inter-Bank Bond Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China's inter-bank treasury bond
trading market has officially begun.
</P>
<P>
The central bank announced June 6 that all commercial banks had
to stop trading treasury bonds on securities exchanges and
securities trading centers nationwide. The inter-bank bond market
will help stem the flow of credit into the stock market, which has
increased speculation there and as a result bank credit risks,
according to market observers.
</P>
<P>
It also helps the central bank use indirect or market-oriented
means to achieve its monetary goals, they said.
</P>
<P>
All treasury bonds in circulation will be traded only on the
inter-bank money market from now on. Its members include 16
commercial banks and 11 urban cooperative banks. The Central Bonds
Registration and Settlement Company is empowered to provide
trusteeship and settlement services for inter-bank trading in
treasury bonds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
