<HEADLINE> Environmental Awareness Improving in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- In the capital of southwest
China's Sichuan Province, 43.5 percent of the residents are paying
greater attention to environmental problems, according to a recent
survey, and 49 percent of the residents are showing concern for the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Only 6.5 percent of the people say they have little concern for
problems of this kind. Most people surveyed are quite aware of the
problems involved in human survival, the need for participation in
environmental protection, and their social responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
The survey asked people what they care most about in the
environment, and how to handle the relation between environmental
protection and economic development, and how environmental
problems will affect the health of later generations.
</P>
<P>
It showed that the chemical industry has done the most serious
harm to the environment, and that automobiles follow with a close
second. In addition, the survey warns about tourism's possible
future effects on the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
