<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Increases Pollution Control Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A report released by east China's
Anhui Province shows that environmental protection in the Huaihe
River valley has improved.
</P>
<P>
The province straddles the middle section of the river and
pollution from its upper reaches has made pollution control work
more difficult. So, since last year, the government has taken a
number of measures to increase pollution controls, officials
say. They studied all pollution sources and asked 2,686 polluters
to meet state standards within a certain period of time.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province shut down 458 small factories with
serious pollution problems, and increased spending on
environmental protection and strengthened local environmental
control departments.
</P>
<P>
The province has gotten nearly 10 million US dollars from
overseas to help with its pollution control work, and the World
Bank has offered 60 million dollars in loans to the province's
river pollution control project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
