<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Kenyan newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times
</P>
<P>
-- The French army began pulling out of Congo Republic capital
Brazzaville Monday as talks on settling a bloody political
dispute in France's former colony were due to start in the
neighboring west African state of Gabon.
</P>
<P>
-- Angola's government could increase diamond production by 70
percent in areas wrested from the control of former rebel
movement UNITA, one of the country's diamond chiefs said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation
</P>
