<HEADLINE> Brazil Score Comeback Win over Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 16 (Xinhua) -- World champions Brazil fought
back from two goals down to beat understrength Mexico 3-2 in an
enthralling Copa America match on Monday.
</P>
<P>
This victory in the group C games has ensured Brazil a place in
the quarter-finals with six points from two games. Mexico have
three and their fate will be decided Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Two first-half goals by striker Luis Hernandez put Mexico on
top. But Brazil replied through Aldair and a superb Romario
effort in the first 15 minutes of the second half.
</P>
<P>
A stunning left-foot strike by Leonardo 10 minutes from the end
sealed the Brazilian triumph in a match that served up the best of
Latin American football in what has been a generally lackluster
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Mexico fielded only about half of their regular team. Brazil,
who do not have to play the qualifiers as world champions, have
brought all their top players. 
</P>
</TEXT>
