<HEADLINE> News From Mercosur Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items from Mercosur countries in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The economy ministers and central bank
presidents of the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) countries will
meet in Asuncion, capital of Paraguay, on June 18.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss the import restrictions imposed
by Brazil on April 1, which have affected the exports of Brazilian
trade bloc partners.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Mercosur education ministers met in Asuncion on June
12 to examine measures to promote the teaching languages in this
regional bloc.
</P>
<P>
They discussed Portuguese teaching in Argentina, Paraguay and
Uruguay and Spanish in Brazil, and the way they would facilitate
the exercise of academic activities in higher education within the
Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Trade between Chile and the Mercosur reached a
monthly average of 405 million U.S. dollars between October 1996
and January 1997, 44 million dollars more than the last monthly
average in the previous four months when the monthly average trade
reached 361 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazil received six billion dollars of foreign
investments during the first five months of this year, an increase
of 76.8 percent compared with the same period last year, the
Brazilian central bank announced.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- On June 11 the Mercosur member countries and
Peru established a work timetable to reach a "4 + 1" free trade
agreement as soon as possible, which would make Peru an associate
member of the Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
Technical meetings will be held in this city in July in which
trade lists will be exchanged in preparation for a final
agreement.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- On June 13 Uruguayan President Julio Maria
Sanguinetti attended the final maneuvers of "Operation Ceibo",
a joint peacekeeping exercise carried out by Uruguayan and
Argentine troops.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, in the Uruguayan beach resort of Las Canas, was
the first by the troops from the two countries to demobilize and
disarm the fighting parties, restore law and order, give
humanitarian assistance and support the preparation of elections.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Uruguay has applied to the Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) for a 123 million-dollar loan to complete
regional integration highways.
</P>
<P>
The loan will also serve to provide maintenance to about 500
kilometers of highways in the department of Canelones.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The Mercosur will approve the admissions of
Venezuela, Colombia and Ecuador at the summit to be held on June
18 in Asuncion.
</P>
<P>
The agreements with the three countries will be in the form of
"4 + 1" towards the formation of a free trade zone in all South
America.
</P>
<P>
Chile and Bolivia are already participating as associate
members of the Mercosur. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
