<HEADLINE> Chilean President to Attend Mercosur Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei is
to join the presidents of the four Southern Common Market
(Mercosur) countries at a summit in the Paraguayan capital
Asuncion on Thursday, Chilean Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza
said today.
</P>
<P>
The presidents, from Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay,
will discuss a common proposal to form a Free Trade Area of the
Americas (FTAA), Insulza told the press.
</P>
<P>
Although Chile is not a full member of Mercosur, it has
associate membership and in the past has only been invited to take
part in the final stages of summit forums.
</P>
<P>
However, Argentina's vice president has previously stated that
Chile should take part in negotiations to form the FTAA on
Mercosur's side and this time, President Frei has been invited to
take part in the summit, Insulza said.
</P>
<P>
Chile's "complete alignment" with Mercosur vis-a-vis the FTAA
negotiations "has always been our policy and President Frei and I
have been extremely explicit about this," he added.
</P>
<P>
"We are very satisfied with the current invitation for
President Frei to attend this summit together with the four
Mercosur presidents of Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay in
the Asuncion meeting," said Insulza. 
</P>
</TEXT>
