<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China's Fuyang City Gets Pollution Control Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Fuyang in the Huaihe River Valley
in East China has closed 186 heavily polluting enterprises and
improved pollution controls at 427 other manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Along with its rapid economic growth, the city's pollution
problems have grown, especially in the Huaihe River tributaries
that run through the city, and there were more than 200 pollution
cases in the city tied to economic losses exceeding 100 million
yuan (about 12.5 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
To deal with this, the city government has given priority to
shutting down serious polluters since 1995, and as a result the
city's environment has seen some improvement.
</P>
<P>
The city increased spending on pollution controls, putting
78.15 million yuan into it during the 1991-1995 period. Ten
chemical enterprises that discharged 70 percent of the city's
industrial waste water have all improved their pollution controls
and the city's industrial waste water discharge is 20 percent
less than the average for the 1990-1995 period.
</P>
<P>
Some factories have also increased their capacity to recycle
waste. The city got a total of 19.7 million yuan from recycling
during the 1990-1995 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
