<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Backs ASEAN Vision Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has endorsed in principle
a draft vision plan on the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN), but indicating some adjustments are needed, a senior Thai
official said.
</P>
<P>
The first draft of the ASEAN economic vision 2020 plan
satisfied Thailand, Thai Commerce Minister Narongchai Akrasanee
said, but noting that adjustments are needed to reflect political
conditions and other non-economic issues.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN economic ministers have approved the plan at a recent
meeting in Jakarta, which is aimed at improving ASEAN's economic
strength and competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Key measures in the plan include waiving of import tariffs
under the ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA), business liberalization,
integration of transport systems and cooperation on human resource
development.
</P>
<P>
The plan also calls on ASEAN to help three new members --
Cambodia, Laos and Myanmar -- to upgrade themselves and reduce the
wealth gap between the rich and poor ASEAN members.
</P>
<P>
The vision plan reportedly will be presented to the ASEAN
leaders' meeting scheduled for December 14-16 in Kuala Lumpur,
Narongchai added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
