<HEADLINE> Private Business Grows Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- There are now nearly 200,000
private businesses in Shenyang, the capital of Northeast China's
Liaoning Province, and the number of people they employ has come
to 320,000.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the growth of the Shenyang's private business
sector is the result of the expansion in its service industry. In
fact, the private business sector has become one of the city's
major sources of revenue.
</P>
<P>
Taxes paid by private businesses last year amounted to 400
million yuan (about 50 million US dollars), accounting for nearly
30 percent of local revenues, official figures show. 
</P>
