<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Rice Exports Decrease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's rice exports during the
first five months this year totaled 1.85 million tons, down 23.5
percent in volume compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The value of the rice exported during January and May also went
down by 12.2 percent, according to the Thai rice exporters'
association.
</P>
<P>
Rice exports in May alone totaled 396,190 tons, while in May
last year, the figure reached 513,318 tons.
</P>
<P>
During the first five months this year, the top importer of
Thai rice was Nigeria which imported 186,180 tons of Thai rice,
followed by Malaysia with 168,281 tons, Indonesia with 167,020
tons and the Philippines with 155,497 tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
