<HEADLINE> More People Injured in Bomb Blast in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 26 persons including
four policemen have been injured so far after a bomb planted in a
bicycle by Tamil rebels was set off Monday in Vavuniya town in
Northern province of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
According to military sources today, more such explosions may
occur as rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
want to divert military attention away from their latest offensive
on the adjoining rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly a joint military-police operation is being
conducted in Vavuniya town to detect rebel infiltrators.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been waging a 14-year war in the north and
east of
the island country in their bid to set up a separate Tamil state.
</P>
<P>
The government forces launched a major offensive code named
"Jaya Sikuru" (Sure of Victory) on May 13 in a bid to recapture 75
kilometers of the main highway between Vavuniya and Jaffna which
runs through the rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
To date the government troops have been able to recapture 16
kilometers of the highway after heavy fighting with rebels.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
