<HEADLINE> Italy's Fiat to Seek Expanded China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian car giant Fiat sees
developing its market in China as a strategic goal for the next
century, group chairman Cesare Romiti said here today.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters after the annual shareholders' meeting that
China, with a population of 1.2 billion, was not only a major
market in reality, but also had great potential given the
remarkable changes in its economy. So it would be foolish to
ignore the market.
</P>
<P>
He said his company had already started working towards
expanding its market in China, especially in the field of trucks
and coaches.
</P>
<P>
Iveco, a medium-sized van and truck maker within the Fiat
group, had set up a joint venture with China's Nanjing Vehicle
Manufacturing Factory which would soon go into mass production, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Fiat is also investing in training Chinese personnel in Italian
technology and language, Romiti told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He said he plans to visit China soon to see the market for
himself. 
</P>
