<HEADLINE> Russian Deputy FM Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian Deputy Foreign Minister
Grigory Karasin said here that Hong Kong's return to China was the
accomplishment achieved under the policies carried out by its
leaders, and a "historic victory for justice."
</P>
<P>
Karasin made the remarks when interviewed jointly by
correspondents from Xinhua and the People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
The deputy foreign minister said the process itself of Hong
Kong's return to China was unique. Though it had been very
complicated settling the Hong Kong issue, and it had taken a
fairly long time, generally-speaking, the transition had been
smooth and without upheaval, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the transition had been solved successfully, and
the interests of all sides had been attended to in the
process. The principles of international norms had been observed,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Karasin said Deng Xiaoping, the general architect of China's
reform and opening up, adopted creative attitudes, and found the
solution to this complicated issue. His "one country, two systems"
concept had provided all sides concerned with the solution to Hong
Kong's smooth transition to its motherland, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that what was important was that the "one country, two
systems" principle would be implemented in Hong Kong, China's
Special Administrative Region, from July 1.
</P>
<P>
Karasin said he believed Hong Kong would remain an active
participant in Russian-Chinese economic cooperation after July 1,
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
