<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Chinese Old Folks Live with Their Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 74.7 percent of China's aged
people are living with their children under the same roof
according to recent findings by the State Statistical Bureau (SSB).
</P>
<P>
The bureau's survey found that 90.5 million Chinese
families have members over the age of 60, and in 67.6 million of
these families elderly people can be found living with their
adult children or other relatives.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that the lives of most elderly people in China
are being supported by family rather than by the society, the SSB
survey says.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, there are still 20 million old people
who do not have children or relatives to turn to and have to live
alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Emergency Preparations in Ecuador in Face of "El Nino" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran authorities will undertake
this week an emergency disaster program to prevent the arrival of
the "el nino" weather phenomenon which will cause floods,
mudslides and epidemics.
</P>
<P>
The Social Welfare Ministry is preparing a campaign to assist
all those who could be affected by the natural disaster, the "El
Telegrafo" newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
Social Welfare Minister Gonzalo Baquero Paret said that
flyers and videos will be used to disseminate the program.
</P>
<P>
El nino, which appears cyclically, warms the waters off the
Pacific coast of Ecuador which later dumps enormous amounts of
rain on the American continent which causes flooding.
</P>
<P>
The National Council for the Control of Narcotic and
Psychotropic Substances (CONSEP, its acronym in Spanish) will
provide two vehicles to be used as mobile hospitals and another
two for transporting food.
</P>
<P>
Social Welfare Ministry authorities are considering a special
program to look after about 4,000 victims in each of the provinces
of Guayas, El Oro and Los Rios.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the situations presented by El Nino
in 1982 and 1992 in Ecuador were taken into consideration for
designing this emergency program.
</P>
<P>
Public Health Minister Asdrubal de la Torre Moran will sign
an agreement with World Bank representatives to initiate an
emergency program and to prevent the outbreak of epidemics caused
by the floods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
