<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TV Series Feature History of Yellow Emperor Period </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The shooting of a 20-episode TV
series featuring the history of the Yandi and Huangdi period has
started in central China's Henan Province, one of the origins of
the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
By employing the research results of this period of history and
the numerous relics and historical documents, the TV series
successfully portrays the achievements of the ancestors of the
Chinese nation 5,000-7,500 years ago.
</P>
<P>
During this semi-legendary historical period, the Chinese
ancients already developed farm production and the manufacture of
bronze and copper; the dragon totem already took shape.
</P>
<P>
The program produces a large amount of facts to illustrate the
distribution and development of the descendants of Yandi and
Huangdi and substantiate the fact that Yandi and Huangdi are
the common ancestors of the people of all nationalities of the
Chinese nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
