<DOCNO> XIE19970617.0268 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile to Host Forum of Asia-Pacific Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of 20 countries
and regions will attend the II forum of Ministers of the
Asia-Pacific region on the development of infrastructure to be
held in Santiago on June 26 and 27.
</P>
<P>
During the forum, the delegates will exchange ideas and
experiences on the improvement of the infrastructures of the
countries taking part in the meetings.
</P>
<P>
The topics that will be brought up will include "Public and
Private Partnerships for the Development of Infrastructure",
"Transportation Management", "Housing and Urbanism" and
"International Infrastructure Networks and the Environment".
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Pacific region is one of the regions with the highest
growth rate in the world since the region accounts for 40 percent
of the world's population and 50 percent of all the economic
activity in the world.
</P>
<P>
The first forum of ministers on the development of
infrastructure was held in Osaka, Japan in September 1995.
</P>
