<HEADLINE> China to Ban Sale of Unregistered Medical Devices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China will prevent manufacturers
from distributing unlicensed medical products starting July this
year, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that these products will also be prohibited from
advertising and from being displayed at exhibitions or any other
public places. Violators will be fined as much as 30,000 yuan
(3,600 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
It quoted an official from the State Pharmaceutical
Administration as saying that nationwide inspections will be
carried out in this respect.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 600 firms making medical devices in China,
and about 10 percent are joint ventures. They turn out 3,000
different products a year.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the new move is to guarantee the quality of
the products. 
</P>
