<HEADLINE> New York Stocks End Record-Breaking Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 16 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks fell slightly
today, halting a six-day streak of record-breaking gains as
investors tried to hold onto their profits.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 9.95 points to close at
7,772.09. At one point, the blue-chip barometer hit a high of
7,795.16, but in the end, it failed to keep up with its blistering
recent pace.
</P>
<P>
The Dow has gained more than 20 percent this year, ending last
week with its sixth consecutive record finish.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues slightly outnumbered advancers by a narrow
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 412.28
million shares as against 566.95 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broad-market indexes were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 list
rose 0.20 to close at a record 893.47. The Nasdaq composite index,
which has lagged other indicators, rose 8.97 to a record 1,432.00.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 0.16 to 465.01. The American
Stock Exchange composite index fell 1.93 to 628.17.
</P>
<P>
Investors pushed prices higher Friday after getting yet another
encouraging report that the economy is not overheating.
</P>
<P>
The string of six straight record closes for the Dow is
impressive but not near the record of 12, set in January 1987,
nine months before the crash.  
</P>
</TEXT>
