<HEADLINE> Annan Proposes to Dispatch New Middle East Special Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan proposed today to dispatch Kieran Prendergast of Britain as
his Special Envoy to the Middle East, said a statement by the
spokesman's office.
</P>
<P>
Kieran, born in 1942, has been serving as Under-Secretary-
General for Political Affairs since January 1997.
</P>
<P>
Letters on the mission had been exchanged between the
Secretary-General and the Government of Israel, and a number of
consultations had been held between the Charge d'Affairs of Israel
and Mr. Kieran on the scope of the proposed mission, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said that the Government of Israel imposed
restrictions on the scope of the mission, which were unacceptable
to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Regrettably, it now appeared the mission would not take place
since the Secretary-General needed to report to the General
Assembly by 25 June, added the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
