<HEADLINE> China, UNDP Cooperates to Combat Desertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in China's drylands
will learn new farming techniques to slow down desertification
thanks to a cooperative program between China and the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP).
</P>
<P>
UNDP is contributing technical assistance valued at 1.1 million
dollars, according UNDP Flash released here today.
</P>
<P>
The flash said that a computer-based information network will
aid communication between farmers, extension agents and
agricultural research institutions in the fight against
desertification, which affects as much as one-third of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The network will also be used to monitor land degradation.
</P>
</TEXT>
