<HEADLINE> 14 S. Leone People Arrested for Coup Plot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The military government of
Sierra Leone said here this evening that it has arrested 14
people including seven senior military officers on suspicion of
the involvement in a coup plot.
</P>
<P>
According to Director of Defense Information Colonel Abdul
Sesay, a member of the Sierra Leone People's Party contacted some
members of the Revolutionary United Front and offered several
bags of rice and two hundred thousand Dollars for them to stage a
coup.
</P>
<P>
Among the 14 arrested people, there are seven civilians
including a one time vice president doctor Sama Banya and medical
doctor Brima Kobba. The seven senior military officers included 4
colonels, two majors and one captain.
</P>
<P>
They were transferred to the maximum security prison in
Freetown and heavily armed soldiers have blocked the adjacent
road, preventing traffic from plying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
