<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Ends Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets mixed today, with both London and Paris ending lower while
Frankfurt hitting a record high.
</P>
<P>
British shares finished lower, as Wall Street's recent bull ran
out of steam and a press report sparked fears of an attack on tax
breaks for pension funds in next month's UK budget. The FTSE-100
closed at 4745.1, down 38.0 points.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares ended at a record high, with the
DAX index lifted by a nearly one-percent rise on Wall Street on
last Friday and the continued support of a firm dollar. The DAX-30
index closed at 3765.11, up 20.67 points.
</P>
<P>
French stocks snapped a three-session winning streak after
investors took profits on news of a long-awaited compromise deal
by European Union leaders to keep the single currency project on
track. The CAC-40 index closed at 2795.87, down 12.65 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
